label.value: abnormal arginase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of arginase activity is abnormal.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'abnormal cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000078).

label.value: decreased arginase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of arginase activity is decreased.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'decreased cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000342).

label.value: abolished arginase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which arginase activity is absent.

label.value: increased glutamate-ammonia ligase activity during cellular response to iron ion starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutamate-ammonia ligase activity is increased during a cellular response to iron ion starvation.

label.value: decreased glutamate dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity during cellular response to iron ion starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutamate dehydrogenase activity using NAPD+ as a cofactor is decreased during a cellular response to iron ion starvation.

label.value: increased protein localization to kinetochore during mitotic M phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is increased during mitotic M-phase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased prospore membrane formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which prospore membrane formation is decreased.

label.value: delayed onset of prospore membrane formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which prospore membrane formation begins later than normal.

label.value: abolished histone H3-S10 phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phosphorylation of serine at position 10 of histone H3 not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: complete but unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation with unseparated chromosomes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid segregation results in the division of chromosomes into two distinct unequal masses containing unseparated sister chromatids, located at or near the ends of an elongated mitotic spindle.

label.value: normal transcription during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription occurs to a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) extent during a cellular response to heat. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be measured.

label.value: abnormal invertase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of invertase activity (beta-fructofuranosidase activity) is abnormal.

definition.value: Secreted invertase activity is usually measured.

label.value: decreased invertase activity during glucose starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of invertase activity (beta-fructofuranosidase activity) is decreased under conditions of glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: normal invertase activity during glucose starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of invertase activity (beta-fructofuranosidase activity) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) under conditions of glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: abnormal protein transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein transport is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein export from nucleus

value.value: A transport phenotype in which the export of protein from the nucleus is abnormal. Export of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Encompasses both export of proteins normally retained in the nucleus and nuclear retention of normally exported proteins. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein export from nucleus during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of protein export from nucleus is decreased when the cell is subject to glucose starvation. Export of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: normal protein transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein transport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein export from nucleus during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of protein export from nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) under conditions of glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to Zeocin

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to Zeocin (phleomycin D1). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of Zeocin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal growth on Zeocin

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing Zeocin (phleomycin D1).

label.value: increased cellular dNTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates (dNTPs) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: normal cellular dNTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates (dNTPs) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased (1->3)-alpha-D-glucan level in periplasmic space

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of (1->3)-alpha-D-glucan measured in the periplasmic space is greater than normal.

definition.value: This term can be used when increased Calcofluor White staining is observed at the cell tip, as Calcofluor White binds specifically to linear (1->3)-beta-D-glucans in fission yeast.

label.value: increased (1->3)-beta-D-glucan level in periplasmic space

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of (1->3)-beta-D-glucan measured in the periplasmic space is greater than normal.

definition.value: This term can be used when increased Calcofluor White staining is observed at the cell tip, as Calcofluor White binds specifically to linear (1->3)-beta-D-glucans in fission yeast.

label.value: normal cellular mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide (MIPC) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein localization to membrane during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to one or more membranes does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation from late origin

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication from late-firing origins is abnormal.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at late replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at late-firing replication origins is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased cell-cell adhesion

value.value: A cell adhesion phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells adhere to each other more strongly or to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: normal protein O-linked glycosylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein glycosylation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein O-linked glycosylation is the addition of a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit to a protein amino acid via a hydroxyl or phenol group, forming an O-glycan.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished homocitrate synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which homocitrate synthase activity is absent.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal, including at sites where forks do not normally pause.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing at G4 motif

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions containing G-quartet (G4) motifs.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing at highly transcribed RNA polymerase II genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions where RNA polymerase II actively transcribes genes.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing at nucleosome-depleted regions

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions where nucleosomes are depleted.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing at tRNA genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal at tRNA genes.

label.value: increased replication fork pausing at rDNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork pausing occurs to a greater extent than normal at ribosomal DNA.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at G4 motif during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions containing G-quartet (G4) motifs. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at highly transcribed RNA polymerase II genes during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions where RNA polymerase II actively transcribes genes. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at nucleosome-depleted regions during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions where nucleosomes are depleted. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at tRNA genes during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal at tRNA genes. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: elongated mononucleate aseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is elongated, has no septum, and contains one nucleus.

label.value: decreased cellular magnesium level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of magnesium ions measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: sensitive to acetaldehyde

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to acetaldehyde. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of acetaldehyde that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal growth on acetaldehyde

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing v.

label.value: increased number of Rad52 foci during cellular response to acetaldehyde

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates is greater than normal during a cellular response to acetaldehyde.

definition.value: Because Rad22 often accumulates at double-strand breaks, consider also annotating to 'increased number of double-strand break sites during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000455).

label.value: abnormal chromosome morphology during cellular response to acetaldehyde

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of one or more chromosomes is abnormal during a cellular response to acetaldehyde.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal chromosome organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal chromosome morphology.

label.value: normal protein localization to kinetochore during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
